reviews.review_text: word up to reviewer below me. I love TC, I love PigPen, I love Keith, I love Brent, I love Vince, I love Bruce.  None of them are the same but it's all still grateful dead, homie.  Appreciate it for what it is or don't listen and shut up.  I stayed away from anything past Keith for a long time because of assholes like you and now I thank god for being able to appreciate it all.  These guys are humans and I love them for that.  By the way...Jerry was pretty sick so yeah he ain't doin' too hot but if you don't feel something in this recording, check your pulse

Reviews of this show   I havent given much attention to the shows from the Summer of '95 tho I spend a little time listening to some of the stuff from Spring. I was only able to catch the boys twice once in Spring, once in Summer 1995. 
 I can understand that nostalgia can influence a rating for a person but I am not that person.  
 I was really hoping the SMR was going to be something spectacular. I have not listened to every one but I have listened to the majority and this version is frankly off. He flubs the vocals big time.
The first set has a few moments that stand out. The Masterpiece is very well done and the Little Red Rooster defiantly  had me shaking my bones early this morning and I think perhaps the best part of the show. 
Personally I would recommend skipping this unless you are like me and are so dedicated at this point that you absolute have to listen to every single show
